<document>
    <header>
        <title>Properties Administation Plugin</title>
    </header>

    <body>
        <section>
            <title>Description</title>
            <p>
                The Properties Administration plugin allows you to add modify the properties for your blog such
                as the name or description for your blog or properties such as enabling comments or trackbacks or
                what file extensions to use when looking for blog entries.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Installation and Setup</title>
            <p>
                In your global
                <code>plugin.properties</code> file, add the following line:
            </p>
            <source>
                edit-blog-properties=org.blojsom.plugin.admin.EditBlogPropertiesPlugin
            </source>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Usage</title>
            <p>
                After logging into the administration console, you may click on the link to "Edit Blog Properties"
                and you will be able modify your blog properties.
            </p>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>

